name: Thundagun
description: A lightning fast performance mod for Resonite. It improves performance by decoupling the FrooxEngine and Unity loops by running FrooxEngine and Unity on separate threads.
author: Frozenreflex

releases.changelog:
IMPORTANT: PhotonDust Particles and World Ambient Lighting are NOT WORKING in this version

## What's Changed
* Fix crashing, yeet legacy particles, update skybox connector by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/96


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.2.1...1.2.2-beta

New patch version. Fixed post processing crashes and other issues. Made UIX less prone to breaking. Fixed particle system crash.

**Warning: This mod is experimental. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* Patch out original post processing update by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/89
* Use Thread.Sleep instead of SpinWait by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/87
* Delay UIX updates until the next FrooxEngine update to probably fix UIX breaking in the dash by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/90
* Fix potential memory leak by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/91
* Fixed Startup Crash due to Resonite's ParticleSystem refactor. Hotfixed by … by @BlueberryWolf in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/94

## New Contributors
* @BlueberryWolf made their first contribution in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/94

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.2.0...1.2.1

New minor version. Fixed settings initialization by removing CameraPostProcessingManager reference and added an "EmulateVanilla" option to improve desktop mode performance. Other improvements include batching completed updates from FrooxEngine, switching to spinwait for lower latency, fixing Linux crashes under Proton, ensuring deterministic builds, and enhancing code readability with formatting.

**Warning: This mod is experimental. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* Missing Link Override by @SectOLT in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/76
* Fix various settings not initializing by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/81
* Proton crash fix by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/83
* Fix crash when desktop viewer is disabled by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/84
* Skip desktop viewer patch on linux native by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/85
* Update packet batching, UIX patch, EmulateVanilla mode by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/78
* Switched to spinwait instead of thread.sleep for less latency by @DoubleStyx 

## New Contributors
* @SectOLT made their first contribution in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/76

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.1.1...1.2.0

New patch version. Adds some new connectors and fixes some existing ones.

**Warning: This mod is a prerelease. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* Patch DuplicableDisplay.Update to run on the Unity thread, fixes desktop viewer crash. Add publicizer package to make accessing private fields easy by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/57
* Fix particles to have the right materials, fix DestroyUnityComponentConnector to call base.Update() first by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/60
* Fix material property blocks, add note that RenderIncompleteUpdates can be glitchy by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/59
* Render queue processor update by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/62
* Update readme links by @Merith-TK in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/63

## New Contributors
* @Merith-TK made their first contribution in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/63

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.1.0-beta...1.1.1

New minor version.

**Warning: This mod is a prerelease. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* Implement VideoTextureConnector by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/49
* add option to render incomplete frames by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/51
* Use custom RenderSettings without Slot refs by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/50


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.0.1-beta...1.1.0-beta

Fixes changes to the MeshRenderer and SkinnedMeshRenderer connectors that introduced flickering.
Cleans up some RenderMaterialOverride code and other code.
Fixes #8. 

**Warning: This mod is a prerelease. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* Add RenderContextOverride<T> and RenderMaterialOverride connector, update some other connectors by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/45
* Fix skinned mesh renderer dynamic bones flickering bug, fix pink material bug, add LODGroup connector, fix render material override, and some cleanup by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/48


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.0.0-beta...1.0.1-beta

Initial beta release. Should be stable enough now for most use cases. UI should hopefully not break anymore, as FrooxEngine will never run before Unity has finished processing changes, and Unity will never process changes until FrooxEngine is done. The main goal at this point is to allow Unity to keep rendering if FrooxEngine doesn't have anything to present, which should boost framerate and protect against hitching in VR.

**Warning: This mod is a prerelease. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* Buffering by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/44
* State guard by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/42


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.1.0-alpha...1.0.0-beta

New minor version. Fixes issues related to UI for the most part. Simplifies/unifies the config usage, exposing settings for min/max engine/Unity tick rates. Should generally be more stable and performant than the previous version.

**Warning: This mod is a prerelease. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* Unify existing systems by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/37


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/compare/1.0.0-alpha...1.1.0-alpha

Initial alpha release. Note that there are known issues with certain connectors for this version. The core behavior does not have any known issues.

**Warning: This mod is a prerelease. It may contain bugs and other issues. Crashes and missing/buggy/jittery visuals are possible but are generally uncommon. Use at your own risk.**

## What's Changed
* add synchronization between frooxengine and Unity by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/1
* Async by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/2
* tweak config names for clarify by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/11
* add author names by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/13
* rough draft for a readme by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/12
* add auto switching by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/15
* run dotnet format by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/16
* remove non-todo comments by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/17
* add desync mode and stall prevention by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/20
* Fix 3d textures and camera portals by @Nytra in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/36
* Prerelease prep by @DoubleStyx in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/31

## New Contributors
* @DoubleStyx made their first contribution in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/1
* @Nytra made their first contribution in https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/pull/36

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Frozenreflex/Thundagun/commits/1.0.0-alpha

releases.changelog: Update for the Splittening prerelease

Rebuild against 2025.2.18.3 due to `FrooxEngine.UIX.UIExtensions.EnsureOptionDescriptionDriver` changes
- Closes #9
Rebuild against 2025.2.18.3 due to `ValueReceiver` being moved to `FrooxEngine.UIX.*` from `FrooxEngine.*` in 2025.2.17.1301
- Rebuild for CommonToolExtensions being renamed to InteractionHandlerExtensions

2024.9.4.357

- Resolve ambiguous match for `RadiantDashScreen.BuildBackground` method

Hotfix for the new type update
 - Handle new `DynamicVariableWriteResult`
 - Fix new ambiguous method call when building
 - Rebuild for compatibility

- Rebuild against Resonite Beta 2024.5.29.130 for compatibility
- Added support for the inspector field action buttons when in VR
    - I made the buttons disabled in desktop due to issues with the context menu locking the user's view in place

## There's nothing new in this version
This is just a rebuild against Resonite Beta 2024.4.15.1407 for compatibility

Initial release for the [Resonite Mod Manifest](https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/resonite-mod-manifest)
- Updated harmony ID to `ninja.badhalo.ModSettings`
- Cleaned up build files
- Fixed config keys not showing if they were defined without using fields - Fixes #2

- Add padding to the mod info footer
- Fix alternating backdrops not showing properly

- Added support for passing field attributes to `SyncMemberEditorBuilder`
  - Most importantly are the Range and Format attributes, allowing for sliders and custom text formatting in your config fields
  - Mod developers need to add the attributes to their `ModConfigurationKey`s
- Fix conditional logic that was overlooked causing #1 - Reported by @Raidriar796 @Nytra

- Generally cleaned up the project
- Added an option to show all mods instead of only mods with supported configs
- Added dash background
- Added projects for test mods

releases.changelog:
- Fixed start world commands creating invalid invites #28
- Fix nml typo in a warning message - #27 by @XDelta

- Added the option to automatically accept invite requests sent using the Ask to Join button (`AutoHandleInviteRequests`)
  - This will send an invite for whatever session the headless is currently focused on
  - This is only done if it is sent directly to the headless by the person requesting, this does not apply to forwarded requests
  - The permission check is handled the same as the `/reqInvite` command
  - If the user does not have permission to join then the request will be forwarded to the session admins

- Discord changes
  - Added `WorldCrashed` event
  - Added option to add go.resonite.com link to session start message (`DiscordLinkToSession`)
  
- Command changes
  - Added ability for `reqInvite` to do partial match
  - Stop `reqInvite` command from reporting full world name if you do not have permission to join
  - Fixed starting worlds with a world orb
  - Fixed start world commands not always reporting a name

- Misc changes
  - Exposed RegisterCommands as a public method
  - Updated project files


##  This requires a version of Harmony for net 9
The official release of dotnet9 harmony is out, you can get it from [here](https://github.com/pardeike/Harmony/releases) or on the [ResoniteModLoader release page](https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/releases)

- Fix Discord Integration #25 
  - There is a known issue where the worlds loaded by the headless config report the wrong name on startup
- Fixed GetSessionOrb command not behaving correctly

##  This requires a version of Harmony for net 9
The official release of dotnet9 harmony is not out yet, for now you can get a temporary version here
https://github.com/stiefeljackal/pardeike.Harmony/releases/tag/temp-release

## Updated to Discord.Net v3.17

- Rebuild against Net9 - https://github.com/New-Project-Final-Final-WIP/HeadlessTweaks/issues/23  https://github.com/New-Project-Final-Final-WIP/HeadlessTweaks/issues/22
- Add hideFromListing command - https://github.com/New-Project-Final-Final-WIP/HeadlessTweaks/issues/21
- Clean up AutoInviteOptOut handling
- Change world name lookup to prioritize world index over name
- Switch to using new C# language goodies


##  This requires a version of Harmony for net 9
The official release of dotnet9 harmony is not out yet, for now you can get a temporary version here
https://github.com/stiefeljackal/pardeike.Harmony/releases/tag/temp-release

- Target framework net8.0
- Update harmony id to match correct domain
- Removed `_configSaved` to address #15 
- Changed some code styles
- Changed some method signatures

- Added owner only command to shutdown the headless
- Fix compatibility with 2024.6.10.1405 - 2024.6.11.74

- Rebuild against Resonite Beta 2024.5.29.130 - fixes #17 
- Temporarily changed back method of checking if headless exists

- Added #13 DiscordWebhookThreadID 
- Switched to using ModLoader.IsHeadless
- Rebuild as possible fix for #14 
- Cleaned up project files


Still Discord.Net v3.12.0

- Fixed issue with saving worlds #11 - Reported by @Renarikun
- Fixed issue with removed contacts not displaying properly #10 Reported by @darbdarb and @sveken
- Fixed issue changing permission level after it had already been set

- Fixed crash on user leave webhook message #8 
- Fix Discord.Net not being properly detected on windows
- Implemented configuration for disabling events #3 - @hantabaru1014
- Implemented configuration for changing event colors
- Re-added EngineStart event - This is disabled by default

Small Update

- Ported to Resonite
- General project cleanup
- Fix a couple small things
- Cleanup wording
- Cleanup and rewrite most commands
- Allow arguments with spaces if they are in quotes
- Speed up initial namespace checks - Fixes #7
- Made commands asking for a user work with username
- Update Discord.Net


# UPDTATED TO DISCORD.NET 3.12.0
# ⚠ Any release prior to 2.0.0 is for [NeosVR](https://neos.com/).

Added Optional SmartAutoSave
 - If enabled, will only save if a user is in the world and once after the last user leaves

Fixed Check for if a user can join a world
 - Allow contacts of headless who aren't moderator or above when world is set to contacts or higher
